#-*- mode: org -*-
#+STARTUP:    align fold hidestars oddeven
#+TITLE:    JILL Real-Time Auditory Neuroscience Framework
#+AUTHOR:    Dan Meliza
#+EMAIL:     dan@meliza.org
#+LANGUAGE:   en

*JILL* is a system for auditory behavioral and neuroscience experiments that
uses the JACK realtime audio framework (http://jackaudio.org). *JILL* comprises
several independent, interacting modules that handle stimulus presentation,
vocalization detection, and data recording.

** Requirements

+ a modern C++ compiler (e.g. g++ 4.4 or later)
+ scons (https://www.scons.org)
+ JACK (http://jackaudio.org; version 1: >= 0.121; or version 2: >= 1.9)
+ boost (http://http://www.boost.org; >= 1.42)
+ libsndfile (http://www.mega-nerd.com/libsndfile; >= 1.0.20)
+ libsamplerate (http://www.mega-nerd.com/SRC/; > 0.1.7)
+ ARF (https://github.com/dmeliza/arf; >= 2.0)

** Installation

JILL comprises a library, a set of headers, and a number of modules.
To compile both library and modules:

: scons -Q library modules

To install the headers, library, and modules in a system location, use
the following command:

: scons -Q install --prefix <prefix>

The default prefix is /usr/local, but this can be changed with the
prefix argument.


